As part of its efforts to boost youth development and empowerment in Nigeria, ALAT by Wema, Nigeria’s first fully digital bank, has announced its sponsorship of the ongoing 26th Nigerian University Games Association (NUGA). The 2022 NUGA Games which commenced on Wednesday, March 16, will run till Sunday, March 27, at the University of Lagos, Akoka,Yaba with over 5,000 athletes from 75 accredited universities competing in 16 sporting events. Participants are drawn from the federal, state and private universities across the country. Aside from sponsoring the ongoing Games, ALAT also renovated the University of Lagos indoor sports center. Speaking on the sponsorship, head of the marketing communications and investor relations, Wema Bank Plc, Funmilayo Falola, said the bank is always eager to support young Nigerians. “ALAT is honoured to be sponsoring the NUGA Games. We are always looking for ways to invest in young Nigerians and sports is one of the pivotal touch-points of Nigerian students. The NUGA Games have united over 47 universities in 26 years, and we are proud to be a part of that rich youth history in Nigeria. “ALAT focuses on being audacious, limitless, inspirational and timeless, and these young sports stars embody these values.”